I would love to have included this Marcia–Shiv exchange, but the velocity
required by the gathering storm of the end of the episode meant we had to lose it.
The end of this episode is a good example of how scripted scenes get improved
by the opportunities afforded on set. At script, I didn’t know what the final image
would be. On set, we found a better sequence for the dialogue and action. Then
Mark Mylod, in collaboration with Sarah and Matthew, found a much stronger final
image than that gestured at here.
